When running the Bamboo agent without an explicit bamboo home, a spurious directory tree is created under {{bamboo-agent-home/bin/}} directory with the following form {{"/home/bamboo/bamboo-agent-home"}}, which can be traversed using bourne shell like so:

{noformat}
bamboo@VictoriaBitter:~/bamboo-agent-home/bin$ cd \"
bamboo@VictoriaBitter:~/bamboo-agent-home/bin/"$ cd home/
bamboo@VictoriaBitter:~/bamboo-agent-home/bin/"/home$ cd bamboo/
bamboo@VictoriaBitter:~/bamboo-agent-home/bin/"/home/bamboo$ cd bamboo-agent-home\"/
{noformat}

I would hazard that this directory is created between the service wrapper and the bootstrap JAR, as all the build information is created under here:

{noformat}
bamboo@VictoriaBitter:~/bamboo-agent-home/bin/"/home/bamboo/bamboo-agent-home"$ ls
bamboo-agent.cfg.xml  xml-data
{noformat}

This is the command line used to launch the agent:

{noformat}
java -Dbamboo.agent.ignoreServerCertName=true -jar bamboo-agent-2.2-SNAPSHOT.jar https://atlassian18.private.atlassian.com/agentServer/
{noformat}

This should really check that the build key length on the _1. Create a new plan_ page will fit in to the data type used by the ORDB; instead it will allow you to complete the process only to be greeted by the *Oops* page.  The logs show that there is a JDBC exception as the build key is longer than 255 characters:

{noformat}
@4000000049825760392c73a4 2009-01-29 19:26:46,959 WARN [TP-Processor60] [JDBCExceptionReporter] SQL Error: 0, SQLState: 22001
@4000000049825760392d2b3c 2009-01-29 19:26:46,959 ERROR [TP-Processor60] [JDBCExceptionReporter] ERROR: value too long for type character varying(255)
@4000000049825760393243ec 2009-01-29 19:26:46,959 ERROR [TP-Processor60] [SessionImpl] Could not synchronize database state with session
@40000000498257603a69933c 2009-01-29 19:26:46,959 WARN [TP-Processor60] [HibernateObjectDao] Problems getting build by key
@40000000498257603a699b0c net.sf.hibernate.exception.GenericJDBCException: could not insert: [com.atlassian.bamboo.build.DefaultBuild#56524807]
{noformat}

But this is what the user is greeted with:
{noformat}
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: object cannot be null
{noformat}

[^Internal server error - Extranet Bamboo.html]

Once this happens, the user must restart their plan creation from scratch.

The method signature I would like implemented in the ElasticAgentManager interface is:

{code}
 /**
     * Validate that the AWS credentials are correct
     * @param accessKey - AWS access Key
     * @param secretKey - aws secret key
     * @return ErrorCollection with any validation errors
     */
    ErrorCollection validateAwsCredentials(String accessKey, String secretKey);
{code}

I have set up bamboo_bot@spartez.com account in general IM configuration (our domain "spartez.com" is managed by google), and all notifications works. But when I test connection when editing IM configuration, I got exception
{panel}
{color:red}XMPP Error encountered while attempting to send message using *bamboo_bot@spartez.com@talk.google.com*:5223, error message is: SASL authentication failed{color}
{panel}

We have been having problems with BEAC agents failing to communicate with the Server and just hanging.  This seems to happen at the same time as Garbage Collection.  From the Garbage Collection logs we see:

{code}
