Those "Unloading class sun.reflect.GeneratedSerializationConstructorAccessor" lines go on forever (~8000 lines).

If a p4 client is mapped like
{code}//depot/Prj/... //newClient/depot/Prj/...
+//depot/Dep/... //newClient/depot/Prj/Dep/...{code}
and the plan's repository configuration | Depot View is
{code}
//newClient/depot/Prj/... {code}
*no* changes to files in //newClient/depot/Prj/Dep/... are picked up by change detection.
The way the change detection (PerforceManager.java) works *now* is that the client view is mapped to the _depot view_. Thus {code}
p4 changes //depot/Prj/... {code} is used.
What *should* be used is {code} p4 changes  //newClient/depot/Prj/... {code} which is the _client view_ 
This will detect changes in  //newClient/depot/Prj/Dep/...
